Fit Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution

Source: R/fit.R
mvn_fit.Rd

Fit Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution

mvn_fit(data, taskid)

Arguments

data

n by 3 matrix or data frame. data[, 1] correspond to values for x. data[, 2] correspond to values for m. data[, 3] correspond to values for y.
taskid

Numeric. Task ID.

See also

Other model fit functions: .fitfiml(), .fitsem(), .fit(), fit(), mvn_fit_simulation_summary(), mvn_fit_simulation(), mvn_fit_task_summary(), mvn_fit_task(), mvn_fitfiml_mar_simulation(), mvn_fitfiml_mar_task(), mvn_fitfiml_mar(), mvn_fitfiml_mcar_simulation(), mvn_fitfiml_mcar_task(), mvn_fitfiml_mcar()

Examples

taskid <- 1
data <- mvn_dat(taskid = taskid)
mvn_fit(data = data, taskid = taskid)
